{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make It Mandatory for Employers to Educate Employees on \"Employment Rights\"",
        "additional_details": "Equality and Human Rights Commission on 21/12/2017 reported that ethnic minorities have a 12.9% higher unemployment rate.\r\n\r\nBlack workers with degrees earn 23.1% less on average.\r\n\r\nIn Britain, only 8.8% of the minorities worked at a manager level or higher.\r\n\r\nBased on GOV statistics from Jan-Sep 2017:\r\n13% of the jurisdictional complaints were related to Equal Pay\r\n11.7% for discrimination of some kind.\r\n\r\nThese numbers are alarming!\r\n\r\nSo please sign the petition and protect our rights.EDUCATE EMPLOYEES",
        "background": "Discrimination at work is a harsh reality of British Labour Market. This is mainly due to lack of training among the employers and lack of understanding of rights among the employees. \r\nThe only way to protect ourselves and next generation is to make it mandatory for employers to educate their staff",
